### Title: Add real test suites to all packages

## Overview

All three packages (`@specsafe/core`, `@specsafe/cli`, `@specsafe/test-gen`) currently have `"test": "vitest --passWithNoTests"` — meaning zero actual tests are required to pass CI. This is a critical gap for a tool whose core value proposition is TDD.

## Tasks

- [ ] Write unit tests for `@specsafe/core` (Workflow, ProjectTracker, validation utilities)
- [ ] Write unit tests for `@specsafe/test-gen` (ScenarioParser, TypeScriptTestGenerator)
- [ ] Write integration/e2e tests for `@specsafe/cli` (all commands: `init`, `new`, `spec`, `test`, `code`, `qa`, `complete`, `archive`)
- [ ] Remove `--passWithNoTests` flag once tests are in place
- [ ] Ensure CI fails on test failure
- [ ] Target meaningful coverage (e.g. ≥80% for core and test-gen)

## Acceptance Criteria

- All packages have real test files
- `pnpm test` passes with actual assertions
- CI enforces test passage

**Priority:** P0 — Blocker for v1.0